Test if an object exists in the namespace of a package.

Source: R/exists_in_pkg.R
exists_in_pkg.Rd

Test if an object exists in the namespace of a package. Useful inside an if statement.

exists_in_pkg(object, package)

Arguments

object

String giving the object to find.
package

String giving the package which namespace to search.

Value

Logical.

See also

Other functions for developers.: check_crucial_names, check_unique, extract_insensitive, insensitive, multiple_var, nms_pull_matches, rename_matches, round_any

Examples

exists_in_pkg("cars", "datasets")
#> [1] TRUE
